  "1881 Napa Valley|Grilled Caesar": "Napa Cab — dark cherry, blackcurrant, mocha, smooth medium tannin. The approachable body meets anchovy-parmesan dressing and the mocha plays against grilled-romaine char. Works as entry Napa Cab for grilled Caesar — unconventional step-up pour on the classic layered salad.",
