  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Chocolate Brownie": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this dense chocolate dessert's deep cocoa richness. Bold whiskey meets rich chocolate — cross-category depth that plays. Strong — dark-on-dark.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Cowboy Ribeye": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. Whiskey depth, oak, and sweetness carry beef weight — the drink scrubs fat and echoes char. Strong — steakhouse classic.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Crab Cake": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. The whiskey sits heavy against a starter; the match depends on whether the plate has fat to scrub. Avoid — too heavy for delicate starters.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Creamed Spinach": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence. Whiskey's oak and sweetness mirror the side's dairy and umami depth. Strong — richness aligned.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Filet Mignon": "Aged super-premium bourbon with the filet — this is the refinement pairing. Elijah Craig 18, Heaven Hill 20, Michter's 10 all carry the oak depth to frame the filet without crushing the cut's tenderness. A pour for the guest who wants restraint over power.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|G.D. Vajra Moscato d'Asti": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat, considered as a bridge into the Moscato's peach-and-honey sweetness with delicate effervescence. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Grilled Caesar": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing. Bold whiskey against the Caesar's char and umami — weight matches, but the flavors compete. Works as a bold-on-bold match.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Kansas City": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this bold, beefy strip's firm texture and savory char. Oak, caramel, and spirit heat stand up to the beef's render; the caramelized sweetness mirrors the crust. Strong — steakhouse classic.",
