  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Seared Scallops": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Bold whiskey's weight meets the starter — register depends on the plate's richness. Avoid — too heavy for delicate starters.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Shrimp Cocktail": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. The whiskey sits heavy against a starter; the match depends on whether the plate has fat to scrub. Avoid — too heavy for delicate starters.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|The Tomahawk": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. The whiskey's barrel depth and the steak's seared fat run at the same intensity — a classic steakhouse move. Works — cocktail-on-steak coherence.",
  "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon|Truffle Fries": "Aged Super-Premium Bourbon: this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat meets this earthy, umami-packed side's mushroom-and-truffle depth. Whiskey's oak and sweetness mirror the side's dairy and umami depth. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Alexander Valley Chardonnay|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Alexander Valley Chardonnay against a spirit-forward bourbon cocktail — oak-vanilla Chard has no hook into bold-proof whiskey weight. Never layer. Keep Chardonnay for the seafood and chicken course; route the Old Fashioned to fatted steaks, marrow, or end-of-dinner spirit service.",
