  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Chocolate Brownie": "Corazon barrel-finished tequila with chocolate brownie — the bourbon-cask influence (Stagg especially) reads like a cask-strength bourbon against cocoa. The agave underneath keeps it from going too sweet. One of the cleanest crossover desserts on the card.",
  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Cowboy Ribeye": "Barrel-Finished Tequila: this añejo tequila's extended oak, vanilla, and caramel smoothness meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. Aged tequila's oak and vanilla meet beef weight — a cross-category steakhouse move. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
