  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Creamed Spinach": "Barrel-Finished Tequila: this añejo tequila's extended oak, vanilla, and caramel smoothness meets this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence. Aged agave's warmth mirrors the side's richness. Strong — aligned depth.",
  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Filet Mignon": "Barrel-Finished Tequila: this añejo tequila's extended oak, vanilla, and caramel smoothness meets the filet's lean, buttery tenderness and delicate mineral edge. Aged tequila's oak and vanilla meet beef weight — a cross-category steakhouse move. Strong — aligned depth.",
  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|G.D. Vajra Moscato d'Asti": "Barrel-Finished Tequila: this añejo tequila's extended oak, vanilla, and caramel smoothness, considered as a bridge into the Moscato's peach-and-honey sweetness with delicate effervescence. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Grilled Caesar": "Barrel-Finished Tequila: this añejo tequila's extended oak, vanilla, and caramel smoothness meets the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing. Spirit or liqueur against the Caesar's umami and char — depends on the spirit's weight whether it lands. Works as a parallel pour.",
  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Kansas City": "Corazon's barrel-finished tequila with the Kansas City — Sazerac rye cask brings baking spice, Stagg bourbon cask brings cask-strength oak, Weller cask brings soft wheat. All three land the strip's char without dulling the agave spine. This is the tequila pour for a guest who usually orders bourbon with steak.",
  "Barrel-Finished Tequila|Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut": "Barrel-Finished Tequila: this añejo tequila's extended oak, vanilla, and caramel smoothness, considered as a bridge into this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
