  "Burrata|St Supéry Sauvignon Blanc": "Napa Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, citrus-forward. Bright acid handles the burrata's creaminess and doesn't fight the balsamic-and-fruit sweetness on the plate. California pivot for guests who want American producers over Loire when pairing with cheese.",
