  "Creamed Spinach|Freemark Abbey Bosché": "Creamed Spinach: this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A strong, texturally cohesive match.",
  "Creamed Spinach|Frias Block 5": "Creamed Spinach: this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's dark-fruit weight locks into the side's fat and umami; tannin cleans the dairy. A strong, texturally cohesive match.",
  "Creamed Spinach|G.D. Vajra Albe Nebbiolo": "Creamed Spinach: this rich, creamy side's dairy-driven indulgence meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. The elegant red's acidity cuts the dairy fat while its cherry lifts the earthy umami. Strong — the wine refreshes the side's richness.",
  "Creamed Spinach|G.D. Vajra Moscato d'Asti": "Piedmont sweet sparkling — peach, honey, floral. The sweetness fights the parmesan-garlic roux and the spinach's vegetal bite on every axis imaginable. Route Moscato to dessert where sugar makes sense — never pour on a savory cream side.",
