  "Domaine Serene Grand Cheval|Bone Marrow": "Willamette flagship Pinot Blend against pure collagen-fat marrow — silky layered Pinot lacks the tannin needed to cut the render. Never pair. Route marrow to Cabs, Bordeaux, Meritage, or structured bold reds; keep Grand Cheval for the filet, chicken, or seafood course.",
  "Domaine Serene Grand Cheval|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Willamette flagship Pinot Blend alongside a bourbon-forward Old Fashioned — silky layered Oregon Pinot has no hook into spirit-weight whiskey. Never layer. Keep Grand Cheval for the salmon and chicken course; route the Old Fashioned to fatted steaks, marrow, or end-of-dinner spirit service.",
  "Domaine Serene Grand Cheval|Burrata": "Willamette flagship Pinot Blend — dark cherry, Bing cherry, toasted spice, forest floor, silky soft tannin. The silky tannin meets burrata's creamy-delicate center and the Bing cherry plays against basil-tomato. Works as flagship Willamette Pinot for burrata — Oregon elegance; whites peak higher for the starter.",
