  "Grand Marnier|The Tomahawk": "Grand Marnier: this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness meets this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression. Sweet or herbal liqueur against a savory plate — register mismatch. Avoid — not a mid-plate pour.",
  "Grilled Caesar|1792 Small Batch": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets spicy-sweet Barton. Works; high-rye doesn't drive the Caesar at 93.7 proof.",
  "Grilled Caesar|1792 Sweet Wheat": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets sweet-wheat. Works; bourbon's character distinctive but pairing isn't a standout.",
  "Grilled Caesar|1881 Napa Valley": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. Works cleanly.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Adictivo Cristalino": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets filtered cristalino. Strong; aged-but-clear character earns the Caesar with distinctive craft depth.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Adictivo Reposado": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets long-aged reposado. Strong; rich oak earns the Caesar where standard reposados only work.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Aged Super-Premium Bourbon": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this bold, high-proof bourbon's oak spice, caramel weight, and heat. Bold whiskey against the Caesar's char and umami — weight matches, but the flavors compete. Works as a bold-on-bold match.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Alexander Valley Chardonnay": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Crisp white acidity cuts the Caesar's creamy umami while mineral edge matches the anchovy. Works cleanly.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Alexander Valley Cyrus": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's structure meets the Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold dressing — weight on weight. Works — the Caesar can hold the tannin.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Alexander Valley Homestead Red": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Amaro / Bitter Liqueur": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this amaro's bitter-herbal complexity and Italian digestif depth. Spirit or liqueur against the Caesar's umami and char — depends on the spirit's weight whether it lands. Strong — the spirit's depth matches the dressing.",
