  "Grilled Caesar|Maker's Mark Cellar Aged": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine and anchovy meet Maker's Mark Cellar Aged's deep vanilla. The Cellar Aged earns the salad where standard Maker's can't.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Marc Brédif Chinon": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Margarita": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this bright tequila cocktail's citrus lift and agave backbone. Bright, light cocktail with the Caesar's bold char — the drink reads thin against the umami. Strong — the interaction lands despite the axis challenge.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Marimar Estate Christina": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. Strong — aligned register.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Mezcal": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets the mezcal's smoky, earthy agave with distinctive mineral bite. Mezcal's smoke and earthy agave against the dish — smoke-meets-fat or smoke-meets-umami are the interesting axes. Strong — aligned depth.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Mijenta Blanco": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets premium craft. Strong; additive-free clean character earns the Caesar.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Milagro Reposado": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets modern reposado. Strong; clean agave finds the Caesar at contemporary everyday tier.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Muga Reserva": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Tannin and char, umami and dark fruit — the bold red and the Caesar punch at the same level. A confident Caesar pour.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Negroni": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this dry, spirit-forward gin cocktail's bitter-herbal complexity. Bright, light cocktail with the Caesar's bold char — the drink reads thin against the umami. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Never Say Die Small Batch": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets UK-aged bourbon. Works; distinctive character worth mentioning tableside even if pairing isn't marquee.",
  "Grilled Caesar|New York Sour": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this bold whiskey-forward cocktail's oak, spice, and spirit depth. Bold whiskey against the Caesar's char and umami — weight matches, but the flavors compete. Strong — both land heavy.",
