  "Grilled Caesar|Not a Paper Plane": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this bold whiskey-forward cocktail's oak, spice, and spirit depth. Bold whiskey against the Caesar's char and umami — weight matches, but the flavors compete. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Odette Cabernet Sauvignon": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's structure meets the Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold dressing — weight on weight. Works — the Caesar can hold the tannin.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Old Fitzgerald 7 Year": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets wheated bond. Works; Old Fitz 9 brings more depth.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Old Fitzgerald 9 Year": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine and anchovy meet 9-year wheated. Strong; aging earns the Caesar where Old Fitz 7 only works.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Opus One": "Mondavi-Rothschild's $950 prestige Cabernet — the dressing's anchovy and egg yolk flatten the structured tannin. Never pour Opus on the Caesar; the wine loses. Reserve for the Tomahawk or Porterhouse.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Our Lady of Guadalupe Acolytes": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Crisp white acidity cuts the Caesar's creamy umami while mineral edge matches the anchovy. Strong — clean foil.",
