  "Grilled Caesar|Pierre Gimonnet Special Club Brut": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Sparkling bubbles scrub the Caesar's creamy-umami fat while acidity matches the citrus notes. Strong — bubbles + umami.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Pineau des Charentes": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets the Pineau's grape-sweet, cognac-warmed aperitif profile. Dessert-register fortified meets savory food — the sweetness usually overruns the dish. Works as a transition from savory into dessert.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Pio Cesare Barbaresco": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The Caesar's anchovy-parmesan depth gives the bold red's tannin something real to work against. Strong — aligned intensity.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Poderi Aldo Conterno Nebbiolo": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Tannin and char, umami and dark fruit — the bold red and the Caesar punch at the same level. Works — the Caesar can hold the tannin.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Pommery Cuvée Louise": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this prestige Champagne's layered complexity — toasty lees, fine mousse, and mineral depth. Sparkling bubbles scrub the Caesar's creamy-umami fat while acidity matches the citrus notes. Works cleanly.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Quilt Cabernet Sauvignon": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. Works cleanly.",
  "Grilled Caesar|RAEN Royal St Robert": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. Strong — aligned register.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Raventós Cava de NIT Rosé Brut": "Rosé Cava — sparkling, red-fruit character. Bubbles cut the dressing's egg-yolk weight, and the rosé fruit survives against our cayenne croutons' heat. Clean sparkling route for a rich salad course — does real work here.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Robert Moncuit Les Grand Blancs": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Sparkling bubbles scrub the Caesar's creamy-umami fat while acidity matches the citrus notes. Strong — bubbles + umami.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Russell's Reserve 10 Year": "Grilled Caesar: charred romaine meets aged bourbon. Works; 10-year earns a bit more of the Caesar than younger non-wheated pours.",
  "Grilled Caesar|San Simeon Stormwatch": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Cherry-driven red with the Caesar's umami and char — a classic cross-category salad pair. Strong — aligned register.",
