  "Grilled Caesar|Sazerac": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this bold whiskey-forward cocktail's oak, spice, and spirit depth. Bold whiskey against the Caesar's char and umami — weight matches, but the flavors compete. Strong — both land heavy.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Scavino Barolo": "Piedmont Nebbiolo — tar, dried rose, firm tannin. Surprisingly the grilled romaine plus parmesan plus anchovy has enough savory depth to meet Barolo. The cayenne in our croutons doesn't scare the wine off.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Schloss Vollrads Riesling": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this off-dry Riesling's stone-fruit sweetness and mineral backbone. Crisp white acidity cuts the Caesar's creamy umami while mineral edge matches the anchovy. Works cleanly.",
