  "Grilled Caesar|Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc": "Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, green, bright. The greenness clashes against the grilled-char and anchovy funk in the Caesar. The acid is there but the flavor profile fights. Keep Stoneleigh for the wedge or the shrimp cocktail.",
  "Grilled Caesar|Teeter Totter Cabernet Sauvignon": "Grilled Caesar: the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The bold red's structure meets the Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold dressing — weight on weight. Works — the Caesar can hold the tannin.",
