  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Burrata": "Anderson Valley Pinot — dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, refined tannin. The medium tannin meets burrata's creamy-delicate center and the mocha plays against basil-tomato. Works as Anderson Valley Pinot for burrata — concentrated Mendocino; whites and rosés peak higher for the delicate starter.",
  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Cowboy Ribeye": "Anderson Valley Pinot — dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, refined-firm tannin, medium body. The refined tannin stretches toward ribeye's big marbled build though body falls short of the cut's fat-and-char demand vs. bolder Cabs. Works as concentrated Pinot for ribeye — Mendocino structure for Pinot-preferring guest.",
  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Crab Cake": "Anderson Valley Pinot — dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, refined tannin. The medium tannin meets crab's sweet meat and the mocha plays against remoulade. Strong Anderson Valley Pinot for crab cake — concentrated red on the shellfish starter.",
  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Faroe Island Salmon": "Anderson Valley Pinot — concentrated, dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, refined tannin. The concentrated structure plays against salmon's oil-rich flesh; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today's build. Peak Anderson Valley Pinot for salmon — cool-climate depth across seasonal preparations.",
  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Filet Mignon": "Anderson Valley Pinot — concentrated-cool-climate style, dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, firm-but-refined tannin, long finish. The refined structure meets butter-tender filet's lean sweetness and the mocha plays against escargot-butter. Peak Anderson Valley Pinot for filet — concentrated Mendocino red on the delicate cut.",
