  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Kansas City": "Anderson Valley Pinot — dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, firm-but-refined tannin, long finish. The refined structure handles Kansas City's lean-bold strip and the mocha plays against beefy char. Peak Anderson Valley Pinot for the strip — concentrated Mendocino red structured enough for the marbled cut.",
  "J Davies Ferrington Vineyards|Mushrooms": "Anderson Valley Pinot — dark cherry, blackberry, mocha, refined tannin. The mocha-earth echoes roasted-mushroom glutamate and the blackberry plays against the earth depth. Peak Anderson Valley Pinot for mushrooms — concentrated Mendocino on the classic Pinot-and-mushroom pairing.",
