  "Jefferson's Reserve|Au Gratin Potatoes": "Jefferson's Reserve with au gratin potatoes — blended elegance against cheese-and-cream. Strong; sophisticated everyday match.",
  "Jefferson's Reserve|Bone Marrow": "Jefferson's Reserve with bone marrow — blended honey and vanilla against umami fat. The blend's smoothness meets marrow without the sweet-on-fat pattern of wheated takes; a refined starter pairing.",
  "Jefferson's Reserve|Brussels and Belly": "Jefferson's Reserve with Brussels + Belly — blended bourbon meets maple-glazed pork belly. The elegance handles the dish's sweetness without the Wellers' wheat-on-maple doubling; a different logic for the same plate.",
