  "Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut|Bone Marrow": "Chardonnay-blend Champagne against marrow's rendered-fat richness — precise acidity is overwhelmed by bone depth. Never pair. Route marrow to big Cab, Manhattan, or Bowdie's Old Fashioned and keep LP Le Cuvée for the seafood tower, tartare, or filet opener.",
  "Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut|Bone-In Filet": "Chardonnay-blend Champagne — precise green apple, lemon zest, whisper of brioche. The vibrant acidity and clean long finish handle bone-enhanced filet's deeper beef character unconventionally; bubbles reset palate. Strong Champagne-with-steak pairing when guest wants precision over classic Cab structure.",
  "Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut|Bourbon-Cask Speyside": "Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut: this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles, considered as a bridge into this Speyside Scotch's sherry cask, honeyed fruit, and elegant frame. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
