  "Mezcal|G.D. Vajra Moscato d'Asti": "Mezcal: the mezcal's smoky, earthy agave with distinctive mineral bite, considered as a bridge into the Moscato's peach-and-honey sweetness with delicate effervescence. Avoid — the two drinks don't flow cleanly together.",
  "Mezcal|Grilled Caesar": "Mezcal: the mezcal's smoky, earthy agave with distinctive mineral bite meets the Grilled Caesar's charred romaine, anchovy umami, and bold creamy dressing. Mezcal's smoke and earthy agave against the dish — smoke-meets-fat or smoke-meets-umami are the interesting axes. Strong — aligned depth.",
  "Mezcal|House Wedge": "Mezcal: the mezcal's smoky, earthy agave with distinctive mineral bite meets the House Wedge's crisp iceberg against creamy bleu dressing. Mezcal's smoke and earthy agave against the dish — smoke-meets-fat or smoke-meets-umami are the interesting axes. Works cleanly.",
