  "Nut Liqueur|Graham's 10 Year Tawny": "Nut Liqueur: this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness, considered as a bridge into this tawny port's oxidative caramel, nut, and dried-fruit complexity. A headliner cross-beverage progression.",
  "Nut Liqueur|Graham's 20 Year Tawny": "Nut liqueur with aged tawny — hazelnut or almond sweetness alongside the port's oxidative nut-and-dried-fruit depth. Same flavor family, different intensities. Classic after-dinner progression when the guest wants to linger past dessert.",
  "Nut Liqueur|House Wedge": "Nut Liqueur: this sweet cream liqueur's dessert-adjacent lushness meets the House Wedge's crisp iceberg against creamy bleu dressing. Liqueur sweetness or bitter-herbal on a crisp salad — wrong register for a starter course. Avoid — not a salad pair.",
