  "Opus One|Chilean Seabass": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this rich, fatty seafood's buttery flesh and delicate-yet-substantial texture. The bold red's tannin shreds the fish's delicate flake, and the dark fruit clashes with briny sweetness. Textbook avoid — this is the classic red-meat-only territory.",
