  "Opus One|Seafood Tower": "Opus One: this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight meets this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
  "Opus One|Seared Scallops": "Collector Napa Cab blend against scallop sweetness — Opus One's firm-tannin Bordeaux blend buries the delicate shellfish. Never pair. Route scallops to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Riesling, or Rosé; keep Opus One for the steak course.",
