  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Beignets": "Schloss Vollrads — Rheingau Riesling, apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry fruit complements beignets' berry jam directly and the acid cuts fried-dough weight; petrol adds unexpected dessert complexity. Strong Riesling-with-beignets pairing — off-dry fruit meets sweet pastry.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Bone Marrow": "Rheingau Riesling against marrow's rendered-fat richness — off-dry German white has no weight to meet bone depth. Never pair. Route marrow to big Cab, Manhattan, or Bowdie's Old Fashioned; keep Schloss Vollrads for bisque, crab cake, scallops, burrata, or the chicken course.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Rheingau Riesling against a spirit-forward bourbon cocktail — off-dry German white has no hook into bold-proof whiskey. Never layer. Keep Schloss Vollrads for bisque, crab cake, scallops, or the chicken course; route the Old Fashioned to fatted steaks, marrow, or end-of-dinner spirit service.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Burrata": "Rheingau Riesling — apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The delicate off-dry fruit meets burrata's creamy-delicate center without crushing and the apricot-peach plays against basil-tomato-pistachio. Peak gateway Riesling for burrata — fruit-lift without the heaviness of Chardonnay.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Butternut Squash": "Rheingau Riesling — apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry apricot mirrors butternut's caramelized sweetness directly and the lively acid cuts the cream base. Peak Riesling for butternut squash — textbook off-dry-on-sweet-vegetable pairing.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon": "Schloss Vollrads Riesling alongside Napa Cab's cocoa-mocha-tannin weight — off-dry German white against Bordeaux-style Cab is incoherent. Never layer. Route Caymus to the steak course and keep Riesling for bisque, crab cake, scallops, burrata, or the chicken course — each wine to its moment.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Cowboy Ribeye": "Schloss Vollrads Riesling against the Cowboy's marbled bone-in ribeye — light off-dry German white crumples under rendered fat and char. Never pair. Route Cowboy to Silver Oak, Caymus, or bold bourbon; keep Riesling for bisque, crab cake, scallops, salmon, or burrata.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Crab Cake": "Schloss Vollrads — Rheingau Riesling with apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry fruit cuts crab's remoulade and the apricot-peach plays against the sweet meat; lively acid cuts the pan-fry. Peak German Riesling for crab cake — fruit-and-acid match, teaching-wine provenance.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Escargot": "Schloss Vollrads — Rheingau Riesling, apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid. The off-dry acid cuts escargot's garlic-parsley butter and the apricot-peach fruit adds dimension against the snail richness. Strong German Riesling for escargot — unconventional but the provenance story holds through the pairing.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Faroe Island Salmon": "Schloss Vollrads — Rheingau Riesling with apricot, peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry fruit cuts salmon's oil-rich flesh; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today's build. Strong German Riesling for salmon across most seasonal builds — classical fruit-and-acid match.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Grilled Caesar": "Schloss Vollrads — Rheingau Riesling, apricot, peach, petrol, off-dry. The off-dry fruit cuts anchovy-parmesan dressing and the acid plays against grilled-romaine char; petrol adds intrigue. Works as German Riesling for grilled Caesar — conversation-starter choice when guest wants something unexpected.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Honey Roasted Carrots": "Rheingau Riesling — apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry apricot mirrors carrots' caramelized honey sweetness directly and the lively acid cuts the glaze weight. Works as Riesling for honey-roasted carrots — sweet-on-sweet pairing; drier whites peak higher on the side.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|House Wedge": "Rheingau Riesling — apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry fruit cuts iceberg-and-bacon weight and the acid plays against blue cheese dressing; petrol adds intrigue. Strong German Riesling for the wedge — conversation-starter wine reframes the classic steakhouse salad.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Kansas City": "Schloss Vollrads Riesling: this off-dry Riesling's stone-fruit sweetness and mineral backbone meets this bold, beefy strip's firm texture and savory char. Lean white acidity can't balance steakhouse fat — the wine disappears against the char. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Porterhouse": "Schloss Vollrads Riesling: this off-dry Riesling's stone-fruit sweetness and mineral backbone meets this bold, beefy strip's firm texture and savory char. Lean white acidity can't balance steakhouse fat — the wine disappears against the char. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
  "Schloss Vollrads Riesling|Prime Tartare": "Rheingau Riesling — apricot, white peach, petrol, lively acid, off-dry. The off-dry fruit-and-acid cuts raw prime beef's iron richness but the fruit register is less aligned than classical whites for tartare. Works as conversation-starter pairing; Sancerre, Chablis, or grower rosé peak higher.",
