  "Seafood Tower|Aviation": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this gin cocktail's citrus brightness and botanical lift. Light cocktail and delicate starter share the same register — fresh opener. Strong — aligned brightness.",
  "Seafood Tower|Avion Silver": "Seafood Tower: raw oysters, shrimp, lobster meet globally-distributed blanco. Strong; filtered clean character provides a through-line at everyday register.",
  "Seafood Tower|Bee's Knees": "Empress Indigo gin with lemon and honey lavender syrup. Honey sweetness against brine works; the Indigo's butterfly-pea color-change adds visual interest next to the tower. Cocktail route for guests who don't want sparkling.",
  "Seafood Tower|Botanical-Forward Craft Gin": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile. Neutral spirit profile means this reads as an opener, not a built pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Seafood Tower|Bowdie's Old Fashioned": "Buffalo Trace muddled with our rum-soaked cherries, orange, and Angostura. Bourbon and cold shellfish don't meet well — the caramel weight buries the brine and delicate textures. Reserve for the steak course.",
  "Seafood Tower|Bruichladdich": "Seafood Tower: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this Islay Scotch's intense peat smoke, medicinal phenol, and bold weight. Whiskey's oak and caramel are only going to land if the starter can carry weight — check the plate. Works as a parallel pour.",
  "Seafood Tower|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon": "Caymus's cocoa, mocha, and velvety tannins — a full Napa Cab with no business near cold oysters and lobster. The structural mismatch is extreme. Save the bottle for the main course, steer Cab-only guests to Champagne here.",
