  "Seafood Tower|St Supéry Sauvignon Blanc": "Napa Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, citrus-forward. Similar function to the Sancerre but California-forward. Bright acid delivers across the full tower of oysters, crab, shrimp, lobster. Pick when the guest prefers American producers over French.",
