  "Seared Scallops|Peju Cabernet Sauvignon": "Seared Scallops: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Elegant red's cherry and silk mirror the starter's register — light-on-light or bright-on-rich depending on the plate. Avoid.",
  "Seared Scallops|Pierre Gimonnet Special Club Brut": "Seared Scallops: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Sparkling's bubbles and acid scrub the starter's fat while the bright frame lifts the plate. A headliner starter pour.",
  "Seared Scallops|Pineau des Charentes": "Seared Scallops: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets the Pineau's grape-sweet, cognac-warmed aperitif profile. Port-style sweetness isn't built to sit with savory plates; the sugar takes over. Strong bridge pour when the dish leans sweet-savory.",
