  "Shrimp Bisque|Jim Beam White Label": "Shrimp Bisque: cream-based seafood meets entry bourbon. Works neutrally.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Jordan Cabernet Sauvignon": "Alexander Valley Cabernet — soft tannin. Unusual for bisque but handles the shrimp-stock depth and holds up against the rich cream base. Good for the table where one guest refuses to leave Cab even for soup.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Joseph Mellot Sancerre": "Shrimp Bisque: this rich, creamy seafood soup's sweet-briny depth over dairy-rich base meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. The wine's acidity cuts the cream, but its weight doesn't carry the soup. Strong if the soup needs brightness.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Keenan Chardonnay": "Napa Chardonnay — apple, lemon, softer oak than Far Niente. Same function, subtler footprint. Handles our 2-3 hour shell-stock cream base and coconut milk without overwhelming the smoked paprika finish. Lighter Napa Chard pivot.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Knob Creek": "Shrimp Bisque: cream-based seafood meets 100-proof high-rye. Works; boldness pushes slightly past what the soup asks for.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Knob Creek Bourbon/Rye": "Shrimp Bisque: cream-based seafood meets blended bourbon-rye. Works; complexity sits beside the soup.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Komos Rosa Reposado": "Shrimp Bisque: cream-based seafood meets rosé-finished reposado. Strong; wine-cask notes sit with the bisque distinctively.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Lagavulin 8": "Shrimp Bisque: the bisque's sea-driven cream meets Lagavulin 8's maritime brine and vibrant peat. The 8-year's brightness prevents the heaviness Laphroaig would bring; the salinity in the dram picks up the bisque's shellfish depth. Strong.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Lalo Silver": "Shrimp Bisque: cream-based seafood meets Lalo González craft. Strong; clean additive-free sits with the bisque at craft register.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Laphroaig 10": "Shrimp Bisque: the cream-base bisque meets Laphroaig 10's medicinal iodine. Too much; the dram's intensity flattens the soup's nuance. Capable only. For Islay-bisque pairings, Lagavulin 8 is balanced, Bowmore 12 is refined.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Larceny Small Batch": "Shrimp Bisque: cream-based seafood meets wheated honey. Works neutrally.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut": "Champagne acid resets between rich, creamy spoonfuls. The bubbles cut the 2-3 hour shell-stock depth without fighting the coconut milk or the smoked paprika. Elegant pour for a substantial soup.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Le Garenne Rosé": "Provence rosé — strawberry, citrus, clean. Works against the bisque but doesn't peak; the Chardonnays and Chablis do more against the coconut milk and the smoked paprika finish. Fine default pour when the guest isn't moving off rosé.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Lemon Lavender Gin Martini": "Shrimp Bisque: this rich, creamy seafood soup's sweet-briny depth over dairy-rich base meets this gin cocktail's citrus brightness and botanical lift. Cocktail against a creamy seafood soup — acidity and lift cut the dairy base while the spirit carries its own weight. Strong — bright cuts rich.",
  "Shrimp Bisque|Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir": "Willamette Pinot — low tannin, dark cherry, forest floor. Savory depth works with the shrimp-shell stock base; the low tannin keeps the soup from losing its delicate cream texture to tannic weight.",
