  "Shrimp Cocktail|Pommery Cuvée Louise": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this prestige Champagne's layered complexity — toasty lees, fine mousse, and mineral depth. Sparkling's bubbles and acid scrub the starter's fat while the bright frame lifts the plate. Strong — palate-cleansing start.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Quilt Cabernet Sauvignon": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. The elegant red's silky frame sits alongside the starter without weight-fighting — the fruit threads through the plate. Avoid.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Raventós Cava de NIT Rosé Brut": "Rosé Cava with red-fruit sparkle. The rosé handles the tomato-forward cocktail sauce's character, and the bubbles clean the palate after each bite. Solid pivot when the guest doesn't want Champagne but does want sparkling.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Robert Moncuit Les Grand Blancs": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this versatile sparkling's bright acidity, toasty lees character, and cleansing bubbles. Sparkling's bubbles and acid scrub the starter's fat while the bright frame lifts the plate. A headliner starter pour.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Russell's Reserve 10 Year": "Shrimp Cocktail: cold shrimp meets aged bourbon. Avoid.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|San Simeon Stormwatch": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. The elegant red's silky frame sits alongside the starter without weight-fighting — the fruit threads through the plate. Avoid.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Scavino Barolo": "Piedmont Nebbiolo — dried rose, tar, firm tannin. The structure clashes with delicate chilled shellfish; the Barolo crushes every element of the dish. Save for the Tomahawk or Filet where it can meet real weight.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Schloss Vollrads Riesling": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this off-dry Riesling's stone-fruit sweetness and mineral backbone. Crisp or off-dry white's acidity lifts the starter — classic opening-course move. A headliner opener.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Scotto Cellars The Lost Chapters": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Elegant red's cherry and silk mirror the starter's register — light-on-light or bright-on-rich depending on the plate. Avoid.",
