  "Shrimp Cocktail|Smooth / Citrus Craft Gin": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile. Clean spirit against a delicate starter — aperitif-register more than pairing. A headliner match — context-driven peak.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Spiced / Flavored Rum": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this spiced rum's sweet, approachable warmth. Aged spirit's oak and vanilla against a starter — depth meets the opening course. Strong — aligned depth.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Spottswoode Lyndenhurst": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame. Cherry brightness and low tannin let the elegant red move with the starter instead of crowding it. Avoid.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|St Supéry Cabernet Sauvignon": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this medium-bodied red's approachable fruit and food-friendly acidity. Elegant red's cherry and silk mirror the starter's register — light-on-light or bright-on-rich depending on the plate. Avoid.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|St Supéry Sauvignon Blanc": "Napa Sauvignon Blanc — grassy, citrus-forward. The grass note echoes our watercress puree's vegetal character, and the bright acid cuts through the cocktail sauce's horseradish. Clean California pour when the guest wants American over Loire.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|St Supéry Élu Meritage": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Stoneleigh Sauvignon Blanc": "Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc, classic green and citrus. Bright and cold, matches the chilled shrimp's temperature and bite. Approachable entry-point for the guest who isn't looking to spend up on the white list.",
  "Shrimp Cocktail|Teeter Totter Cabernet Sauvignon": "Shrimp Cocktail: this delicate seafood starter's briny-fresh sweetness meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. Delicate seafood or mild creams buckle under the bold red's tannin. Avoid — register mismatch.",
