  "The Tomahawk|Joseph Mellot Sancerre": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this crisp white's citrus-driven acidity and mineral edge. Lean white acidity can't balance steakhouse fat — the wine disappears against the char. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
  "The Tomahawk|Jubilation by Colgin": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The tannin scrubs rendered fat while dark fruit echoes the savory char. A headliner steakhouse pour.",
  "The Tomahawk|Keenan Chardonnay": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this rich, oak-aged Chardonnay's butter, stone fruit, and full-bodied weight. Rich Chardonnay weight approaches steak territory, but the absence of tannin and the oak sweetness clash with the char. Avoid — Chardonnay isn't the steak answer.",
  "The Tomahawk|Knob Creek 12 Year": "The Tomahawk: bone-in ribeye meets 12-year 100-proof. Strong; aged weight handles cut but Baker's 107-proof or Four Roses Select's 104-proof bring more grip.",
  "The Tomahawk|Komos Rosa Reposado": "The Tomahawk: massive cut meets luxury pink reposado. Avoid; rosa reposados are cold-seafood and light-cuts territory.",
  "The Tomahawk|Lagavulin 8": "The Tomahawk: the bone-in ribeye's massive scale meets Lagavulin 8's bright phenolics. The 8-year's brightness carries the cut without feeling heavy; the Islay marquee for guests who want peat with a max-impact cut but not the full medicinal weight of Laphroaig.",
  "The Tomahawk|Lail Vineyards Blueprint": "Polished blackcurrant, cedar, dark cherry with refined tannins. Lighter than the tomahawk could handle, but Robin Lail's Napa lineage adds weight to the story. A relationship pour for guests who want the history.",
  "The Tomahawk|Lail Vineyards Daniel Cuvée": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The tannin scrubs rendered fat while dark fruit echoes the savory char. A headliner steakhouse pour.",
  "The Tomahawk|Lalo Silver": "The Tomahawk: bone-in ribeye meets craft blanco. Avoid; bourbon or scotch territory.",
  "The Tomahawk|Laphroaig 10": "The Tomahawk: the cut's full scale meets Laphroaig 10's full phenolic punch. Seaweed and iodine cut through the marbling in a way no other peated Islay touches. This is the Islay marquee with max-impact beef — when a guest wants peated scotch AND the biggest cut, pour Laphroaig.",
  "The Tomahawk|Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this sparkling rosé's strawberry-and-brioche charm with crisp acidity. Bubbles scrub fat well, but sparkling lacks the dark-fruit weight and tannin for steak. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
