  "The Tomahawk|Le Garenne Rosé": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this dry Provence-style rosé's red-fruit freshness and light weight. Lean white acidity can't balance steakhouse fat — the wine disappears against the char. Avoid — not a steak wine.",
