  "The Tomahawk|Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this elegant red's cherry-bright, silky-tannin frame. The elegant red's medium-light frame gets overrun by the bold, marbled steak — the wine shrinks. Avoid — the elegant red can't carry the weight.",
  "The Tomahawk|Local Michigan Gin": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this contemporary gin's floral, fruit-forward botanical profile. Clean, neutral spirit on a bold steak — wrong weight class entirely. Avoid — not a steak spirit.",
  "The Tomahawk|London Dry Gin": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this London Dry gin's juniper-forward, citrus-herbal frame. Clean, neutral spirit on a bold steak — wrong weight class entirely. Avoid — not a steak spirit.",
  "The Tomahawk|Macauley Petite Syrah": "The Tomahawk: this marbled ribeye's fatty richness, smoky crust, and bold beef expression meets this structured red's cassis-and-dark-fruit frame, firm tannin, and oak-driven weight. The tannin scrubs rendered fat while dark fruit echoes the savory char. A headliner steakhouse pour.",
