  "Woodford Reserve|Brussels and Belly": "Woodford Reserve with Brussels + Belly — fruit-forward bourbon meets maple-glazed pork belly. Woodford's fruit notes play with the dish's maple in a way BT or Maker's can't; a refined small-plate pour.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Burrata": "Woodford Reserve with burrata — fresh dairy against fruit-forward bourbon. Avoid.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Carrot Cake": "Woodford Reserve with carrot cake — small-batch fruit and floral against cream cheese and cinnamon. The bourbon's fruit character picks up the cake's raisins; a distinctive dessert pairing within the everyday premium tier.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Cheesecake": "Woodford Reserve with cheesecake — small-batch fruit notes against clean custard. Works; the fruit character gives the dessert a subtle counterpoint.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Chocolate Brownie": "Woodford Reserve with the chocolate brownie — fruit-forward bourbon against cocoa. Works; for cocoa interplay reach for Weller 107 or Weller Millennium; Woodford's fruit is a different pairing logic.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Cowboy Ribeye": "Woodford Reserve with the Cowboy Ribeye — small-batch fruit-forward against cap fat and char. Strong; Woodford's elegance is slightly underserved by the ribeye's scale — BT or Weller 12 are firmer calls for max-impact cuts.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Crab Cake": "Woodford Reserve with crab cake — small-batch against delicate crab. Avoid; choose a white wine.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Creamed Spinach": "Woodford Reserve with creamed spinach — small-batch fruit and floral against dairy. Strong; the non-wheated profile with fruit notes gives the side a different dimension than caramel-wheat does.",
  "Woodford Reserve|Filet Mignon": "Woodford Reserve with the filet — Kentucky's small-batch classic. 90.4 proof with fruit-forward and floral notes layered over clean caramel. Distinct from Buffalo Trace's straight-line oak — more interplay, more fruit vocabulary. A refined non-wheated call for filet orders.",
